98
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:28,200
of our existence as God's people in the world

99
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:30,120
And there's some analogy here

100
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:33,800
to things, human artifacts

101
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,760
Because the only way to explain

102
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:37,720
what something is

103
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,240
if it's been manufactured

104
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:42,080
is to understand what it's for

105
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:43,120
You could have a clock

106
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,160
and you could describe it

107
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:45,720
I have a little one here

108
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,960
It's a little box

109
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:48,320
It's got a funny little face

110
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,080
It's got numbers up to 12

111
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:50,880
Why only 12?

112
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:52,880
It's got two hands that go round and round

113
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:57,040
But you haven't said what it is as a clock

114
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:59,680
Until you say, ah, well, it's for telling the time

115
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,480
That's its purpose of existence

116
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:04,320
Is to help you know what time it is

117
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:05,880
What is the purpose for which

118
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:08,600
it's been designed and produced

119
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,000
And so therefore we must ask

120
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,440
if we claim that our identity

121
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:14,400
is a people who are created by God

122
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:16,120
as we said in our first lecture

123
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:18,800
We have to further ask, yes, for what purpose

124
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,520
What are we here for

125
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:22,720
What is the reason for our existence

126
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:23,800
and the purpose of being

127
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:26,160
this unique people on the planet

128
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:28,320
Or perhaps better to ask

129
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:30,800
what was the purpose and goal

130
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,720
objective of God himself

131
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:34,320
the God of the Bible

132
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:36,640
for which and within which

133
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:40,680
he chose to create us as his people

134
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:42,360
What is the mission of God

135
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,800
to quote the title of a book

136
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:46,120
that was just mentioned

137
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:47,960
Well, the apostle Paul, of course, gives us

138
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:49,640
what I think is perhaps the most

139
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:53,400
succinct statement of the mission of God

140
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:56,640
in Ephesians 1, verses 9 and 10

141
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:57,880
where God says

142
00:05:57,880 --> 00:06:00,120
just a moment, I need to bring that on there, yes

143
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,800
where God says this, I'm quoting

144
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,840
or Paul says this, I'm quoting him

145
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:06,080
he says, "God has made known to us

146
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:07,720
the mystery of his will

147
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,120
according to his good pleasure

148
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:11,640
which he purposed in Christ"

149
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:12,640
So when Paul's talking about

150
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:13,600
the will of God there

151
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:15,440
he doesn't mean his will for my life

152
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:17,800
He's talking about God's great plan and purpose

153
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,880
"to be put into effect

154
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,920
when the times reach their fulfilment

155
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:23,240
to bring unity to all things

156
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:26,760
in heaven and on earth under Christ"

157
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:28,080
And when Paul says

158
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:29,960
all things in heaven and earth

159
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:30,600
he means it

160
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,880
He's talking about the whole creation

161
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:34,880
And so God's plan, says Paul

162
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:38,280
is to bring unity, reconciliation, healing

163
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:40,360
to the whole creation

164
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,960
in and through Christ

165
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:43,440
That's the mission of God

166
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:45,960
It's the redemption, the reconciliation

167
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:48,080
of the creation that has been broken

168
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:50,400
and fractured by sin and evil

169
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,840
into the new creation

170
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:54,720
which will be populated by the redeemed

171
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:57,480
from every culture, tribe and nation

172
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:59,040
through the cross and the resurrection

173
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:01,360
of our Lord Jesus Christ

174
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:02,480
I think that that

175
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:04,840
that expression there in Ephesians 1

176
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:06,680
is what Paul probably meant

177
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:09,120
when he talked about in Acts 20

178
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:11,920
about the whole counsel of God

179
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,360
which he said he had preached

180
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:15,320
to the people in Ephesus

181
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:17,360
in Acts 20, verse 27

182
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,760
He means the plan of God

183
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:20,000
the purpose of God

184
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,440
from what we would say

185
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:23,240
from Genesis to Revelation

186
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:25,520
the whole grand narrative of Scripture

187
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,360
creation, fall, redemption

188
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,280
and new creation

189
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:32,440
all embraced and held together by Christ

190
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:34,160
So the mission of God then

191
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:36,480
is fundamentally the activity of God

192
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:38,320
driving this story forward

193
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:39,520
from its beginning

194
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,040
through its multiple facets

195
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,640
in the scriptural story

196
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:45,080
bringing it to its conclusion

197
