326
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,040
on the day of Pentecost

327
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:08,160
but began right back with Abraham

328
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:10,880
when God called the people into existence

329
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:12,840
But just as the church didn't begin

330
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:14,560
on the day of Pentecost

331
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:17,440
Christian mission didn't begin

332
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:19,160
on the Mount of Ascension only

333
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:21,520
at the end of Matthew's Gospel

334
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:23,640
The mission of God's people began

335
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:26,880
when God announced his intention

336
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,320
through Abraham

337
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:30,840
to bless not only him and his people

338
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:33,360
but all the nations on earth through him

339
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,720
That's God's mission

340
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:37,200
That's really where we trace it back to

341
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:39,880
Let me remind you of those verses

342
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,640
Genesis chapter 12 verses 1 to 3

