00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:13,160
Many many more

458
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:15,040
Those are just a sampling

459
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:17,840
So when we turn to the New Testament then

460
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:19,240
It's fascinating isn't it?

461
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:22,280
The very first verse of Matthew's Gospel

462
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:24,160
Traces the ancestry of Jesus

463
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:26,520
Not just back to David

464
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:29,880
Israel's messianic king in prophecy

465
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:31,840
But to Abraham

466
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:35,800
So Matthew begins with Abraham in the first verse

467
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:39,760
And ends with a strongly Abrahamic word of Jesus

468
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:40,680
In the Great Commission

469
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:41,840
Where he tells his disciples

470
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:44,760
To go and make disciples of all nations

471
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:46,200
Rather like Paul who speaks about

472
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:48,600
The obedience of faith among all nations

473
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:51,280
It's very Abrahamic

474
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:53,280
Here's how a New Testament scholar

475
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:54,560
Richard Baucom

476
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:56,200
A very fine New Testament scholar

477
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,840
Puts it on our quote

478
00:16:57,840 --> 00:17:00,440
He says Matthew frames

479
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:02,560
The whole story of Jesus

480
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:04,720
Between the identification of him

481
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:06,560
As a descendant of Abraham

482
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:08,640
In the opening verse of the Gospel

483
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:10,960
And in the closing words of Jesus

484
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,400
At the end of the Gospel

485
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,920
With the commission to the disciples

486
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:16,120
To make disciples of all nations

487
00:17:16,120 --> 00:17:17,320
For Matthew

488
00:17:17,320 --> 00:17:18,640
Jesus is the Messiah

489
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:20,360
Not only for Jews

490
00:17:20,360 --> 00:17:22,640
But also for Gentiles

491
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:24,640
He is the descendant of Abraham

492
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:26,560
Through whom God's blessing

493
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:29,240
Will at least at last reach the nations

494
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:31,520
So mission to the nations

495
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:32,600
As we would put it

496
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,920
Evangelization of the world and all of that

497
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:37,560
Is not some kind of afterthought

498
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:38,840
That occurred to Jesus

499
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:40,480
On the Mount of Ascension

500
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:41,560
When he suddenly thought

501
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:43,320
Hey I'm going off back up to heaven

502
00:17:43,320 --> 00:17:44,720
What are these guys going to do

503
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:45,480
With the rest of their life

504
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:46,760
Hey why don't you go and be missionaries

505
00:17:46,760 --> 00:17:47,880
That's a good idea

506
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:49,400
A sort of afterthought

507
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:50,520
At the end of the Gospels

508
00:17:50,520 --> 00:17:52,160
No, it's the climax

509
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:52,880
It's the point

510
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:55,440
It's what the Gospel is all about

511
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,800
That what God had now accomplished

512
00:17:57,800 --> 00:18:01,000
Through the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ

513
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:03,200
Must now become the source of blessing

514
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,280
To all nations

515
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:08,080
So that God could keep his promise to Abraham

516
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:09,480
So in other words therefore

517
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:11,680
There's this theological affirmation

518
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:13,920
That if we are in Christ

519
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:16,080
Then not only as Paul says in Galatians

520
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:17,880
Are we the seed of Abraham

521
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:20,000
We share the blessing of Abraham

522
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,040
We are also commissioned to spread

523
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:25,120
The blessing of Abraham

524
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:28,240
Indeed I would argue that there is something

525
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:30,200
Great commission-ish

526
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,280
That's a word

527
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:34,840
About the Genesis 12 1-3

528
00:18:34,840 --> 00:18:37,560
I'm not suggesting that it's sort of exactly the same

529
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:42,360
But the language certainly bears that sort of flavour

530
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:45,040
It starts with command go

531
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:47,080
It also says be a blessing

532
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:50,160
That middle line is actually an imperative

533
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:51,680
Not just you will be a blessing

534
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:53,000
But be a blessing

535
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:53,840
And then it ends with

536
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:56,400
All nations will be blessed through you

537
00:18:56,400 --> 00:19:01,560
So here is a kind of a dynamic impulse

538
00:19:01,560 --> 00:19:03,600
In which Abraham has launched into the world

539
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:06,240
In order to become as it were the launch pad

540
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:09,400
Of God bringing blessing into the world

541
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:12,200
So the people whom God creates in Abraham

542
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:14,320
Are not only a people for God

543
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:16,600
Belonging to God as we were thinking earlier

544
00:19:16,600 --> 00:19:19,280
But also a people for the world

545
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:23,600
Our identity is also our mission

546
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:26,680
In other words Genesis 12 1-3

547
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:29,320
Is both ecclesiological

548
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:31,920
It's the beginnings as it were of the people of God

549
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:34,160
It's also missiological

550
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:35,840
Because it describes the very purpose

551
00:19:35,840 --> 00:19:38,880
Through which they exist

552
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:42,160
And this Abrahamic dimension of Christian mission

553
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:46,000
Impacts not just that Gentile mission

554
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,200
In the book of Acts

555
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:50,400
Where Paul sees the moving out to the Gentiles

556
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:52,680
As God keeping his promise to Abraham

557
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:55,280
But I would say would be the kind of mantra

558
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:58,520
That one could put over all the following centuries

559
00:19:58,520 --> 00:20:01,280
Of Christian mission ever since

560
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:04,880
You could argue that Christian mission at its simplest

561
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:09,320
Is simply a matter of God keeping his promise to Abraham

562
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:11,160
Which he began to do of course

563
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:12,160
In the book of Acts

564
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:14,360
And then in the New Testament era

565
00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:16,080
So that the gospel went south

566
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:18,600
Down to Africa with the Ethiopian eunuch

567
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:22,520
It goes east according to the church in India

568
00:20:22,520 --> 00:20:25,640
With Thomas who brought the gospel to India

569
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:28,040
And there's certainly documentary evidence

570
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:30,840
Of Christianity in India from the second century

571
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:32,960
It also of course went eastwards to Syria

572
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,360
And then northeast

573
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:35,600
And it was Syrian missionaries

574
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,200
Who were bringing the gospel to China

