00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,480
As I'm sure you know

576
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:40,240
By the 6th to 8th century

577
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:42,040
Went west with the apostle Paul

578
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:44,280
Cross the Bosporus into Europe

579
00:20:44,280 --> 00:20:47,200
And eventually reached the very edges of the world

580
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:49,800
Ireland where I come from

581
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:52,160
On those little islands just off the edge

582
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:54,040
About to drop off the edge of the world

583
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:55,360
And of course ever since

584
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:58,240
Every time the gospel crosses a barrier

585
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,880
Reaches new people

586
00:20:59,880 --> 00:21:03,280
God is keeping his promise to Abraham

587
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:04,960
Bringing the blessing of salvation

588
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:07,600
To new nation after new nation

589
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,600
Until the day comes

590
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,200
That we read about in Revelation

591
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:13,160
Revelation 7 verse 9

592
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:13,920
Where John says

593
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:15,320
I saw a great multitude

594
00:21:15,320 --> 00:21:16,720
That no one could count

595
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:21,120
From every tribe, nation, people and language

596
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:24,680
Standing before the throne of God and the Lamb

597
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:28,360
And I have a kind of mental picture of God

598
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:30,360
Poking Abraham in the ribs and saying

599
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:33,320
There you are, I kept my promise

600
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:35,280
All nations I said

601
00:21:35,280 --> 00:21:37,280
All nations it is

602
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:39,000
Mission accomplished

603
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,840
So that's the first, this missional blessing

604
00:21:41,840 --> 00:21:45,240
The Abrahamic dimension of Christian mission

605
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:47,560
And there's a lot more about that of course

606
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:49,440
In my two books

607
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:51,360
That leads us to the second theme

608
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:52,120
That I wanted to bring

609
00:21:52,120 --> 00:21:53,680
Which is missional priesthood

610
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:56,160
Moving on from Genesis to Exodus

611
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:57,800
We won't go all the way through the Old Testament

612
00:21:57,800 --> 00:22:01,600
But at least we do the first two or three books

613
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:05,040
God's address to Israel at Mount Sinai

614
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:06,720
Comes after the Exodus

615
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:08,200
After they get out of Egypt

616
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:10,480
In Exodus chapter 19

617
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:12,120
And here again we pick up

618
00:22:12,120 --> 00:22:14,800
One of those identities of God's people

619
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:15,720
We mentioned it

620
00:22:15,720 --> 00:22:18,320
I mentioned it in passing in the earlier lecture

621
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:20,160
Of being God's priesthood

622
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:21,680
But let me read these verses to you

623
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:24,200
Exodus chapter 19 verses 3 to 6

624
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:27,560
And the first two verses of the chapter

625
00:22:27,560 --> 00:22:30,040
Give us both the date and the location

626
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:32,520
It says this was just three months

627
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:34,560
After they had come out of Egypt

628
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:37,080
When they had reached Mount Sinai

629
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:40,440
And camped there at the foot of Mount Sinai

630
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:41,120
And verse 3

631
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:42,960
Then Moses went up to God

632
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:45,000
And the Lord called to him from the mountain

633
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:46,480
Mount Sinai and said

634
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:47,800
This is what you are to say

635
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,320
To the descendants of Jacob

636
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:52,640
And what you are to tell the people of Israel

637
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:56,320
You yourselves have seen what I did to Egypt

638
00:22:56,320 --> 00:22:58,400
And how I carried you in eagles' wings

639
00:22:58,400 --> 00:23:00,360
And brought you to myself

640
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:03,040
Now then if you will obey me fully

641
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:04,520
And keep my covenant

642
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:06,480
Then out of all nations

643
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:08,520
You will be my treasured possession

644
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:10,800
For the whole earth is mine

645
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,280
And you will be for me

646
00:23:12,280 --> 00:23:14,040
A kingdom of priests

647
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:15,800
And a holy nation

648
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:17,280
These are the words you are to speak

649
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:18,600
To the Israelites

650
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:20,880
End of quote from verse 6

651
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:22,880
So the very first thing that God does here

652
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:25,160
Is that he points to his own initiative

653
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:25,920
In verse 4

654
00:23:25,920 --> 00:23:28,600
You have seen what I have done

655
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:30,360
Says God in verse 4

656
00:23:30,360 --> 00:23:32,960
In other words this is the priority of God's grace

657
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:35,960
As I said also earlier about election

658
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:39,320
God redeems his people out of Egypt

659
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:42,360
And then talks about obeying him

660
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:43,720
And keeping the covenant

661
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:46,080
Redemption, salvation comes first

662
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:47,680
God's initiative of grace

663
00:23:47,680 --> 00:23:50,120
And then obedience as a response to that

664
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:51,960
In the keeping of the law

665
00:23:51,960 --> 00:23:55,120
And so the motivating power for all that follows

666
00:23:55,120 --> 00:23:57,320
Including the Ten Commandments and the rest of the law

667
00:23:57,320 --> 00:24:00,600
Is always what God has done for them

668
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:02,320
His redemption from slavery

669
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:04,760
The Exodus becomes the motivating power

670
00:24:04,760 --> 00:24:06,800
Why should we keep this law

671
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:09,080
Because God redeemed us out of Egypt

672
00:24:09,080 --> 00:24:12,720
That's the theme that flows through the rest of the law

673
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:16,680
But then, and one could go on a lot about that point

674
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:19,480
But then the text there in Exodus 19

675
00:24:19,480 --> 00:24:22,640
Moves on from that backward looking motivation

676
00:24:22,640 --> 00:24:25,080
What God had already done

677
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:28,280
In 18 chapters of salvation

678
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:31,080
Moves on to a forward looking motivation

679
00:24:31,080 --> 00:24:33,880
That is what God planned for Israel

680
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:36,080
To be in the world

681
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:37,360
In the midst of the nations

682
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:40,280
Here's my agenda for you

683
00:24:40,280 --> 00:24:42,880
This is what you will be for me

684
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:43,960
This is a future

685
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:45,920
This is a looking forward

686
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:50,200
It is indeed what we might call a missional perspective

687
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:52,760
Because God's plan for his people

688
00:24:52,760 --> 00:24:56,200
Is that they should be a priestly and holy people

689
00:24:56,200 --> 00:25:00,480
In the midst of all nations in the whole earth

690
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:01,920
Verse 5

691
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:04,800
Which as I hope you will detect by now

692
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:07,240
Has a certain Abrahamic ring about it

693
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:08,360
God had said to Abraham

694
00:25:08,360 --> 00:25:11,720
I'm going to bless all nations in the earth through you

695
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:14,160
And here is Yahweh God as it were

696
00:25:14,160 --> 00:25:15,920
At the top of Mount Sinai

697
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:18,640
Saying to the people of Israel so to speak

698
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:20,680
From up here as it were in the top

699
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:23,040
I can see the whole earth and it's all mine

700
00:25:23,040 --> 00:25:25,440
And all the nations of the earth belong to me

701
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:28,480
But you will have a particular purpose

702
00:25:28,480 --> 00:25:31,720
A particular identity and agenda in that world

703
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:35,040
To be a priestly and a holy people

704
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:38,080
Now that identity of being priestly and holy

705
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:40,240
Is something which echoes on

706
00:25:40,240 --> 00:25:41,840
Through other parts of the Old Testament

707
00:25:41,840 --> 00:25:45,520
And indeed is inherited by us as Peter says

708
00:25:45,520 --> 00:25:48,880
And will still be there in the book of Revelation

709
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:49,920
But we need to ask

710
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:52,520
What does it mean for Israel

711
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:56,600
To be God's priesthood in relation to the nations

712
00:25:56,600 --> 00:25:58,400
And in order to understand that

713
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,760
We need to ask

714
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:02,640
Well what were Israel's priests for them

715
00:26:02,640 --> 00:26:04,920
How did the priests function

716
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:06,560
And here is one way that I sometimes

717
00:26:06,560 --> 00:26:08,800
Try to illustrate that for you

718
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:11,520
Priests basically were middle men

719
00:26:11,520 --> 00:26:14,520
They stood in between God on the one hand

720
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:17,120
And all the rest of the people on the other

721
00:26:17,120 --> 00:26:18,960
Sometimes we use the word mediator

722
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:20,800
Or in the middle

723
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:23,800
And in that mediating position between God

724
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:25,920
And the rest of the Israelites

725
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:28,760
They had two main jobs

726
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:30,720
One which we don't often think about

727
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:32,400
Was that they were to be teachers

728
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:34,920
Teachers of God's law to the people

729
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:36,960
That's actually what is said about them

730
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:40,680
Right at the very ordination of Aaron and his sons

731
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:41,800
The Lord says to Aaron

732
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:45,120
This is in Leviticus chapter 10

733
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:46,640
He says they must distinguish

734
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:47,960
Between the holy and the common

735
00:26:47,960 --> 00:26:49,240
The unclean and the clean

736
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:52,040
So that you can teach the Israelites

737
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:54,480
All the decrees that the Lord has given them

738
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:55,120
Through Moses

739
00:26:55,120 --> 00:26:56,760
The priests were to be teachers

740
00:26:56,760 --> 00:26:58,160
So that the people would come to know

741
00:26:58,160 --> 00:26:59,560
The ways of God

742
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:02,280
That's also there in the blessing of Moses

743
00:27:02,280 --> 00:27:06,720
On the tribe of Levi in Deuteronomy chapter 33

744
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:08,720
Where it says about Levi

745
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:10,480
Which was the Levites tribe

746
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:12,160
That the priests came from

747
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:14,440
He teaches your precepts to Jacob

748
00:27:14,440 --> 00:27:16,160
And your law to Israel

749
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:18,560
And he offers incense before you

750
00:27:18,560 --> 00:27:20,440
And whole burnt offerings on your altar

751
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:23,600
So the teaching function actually comes first

752
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:26,000
That through the priests

753
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:30,040
God would become known to the people

754
00:27:30,040 --> 00:27:33,800
Which is why when the people went so badly wrong

755
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:35,840
In later life of Israel

756
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:37,520
Who did the prophets blame?

757
00:27:37,520 --> 00:27:38,760
The priests

758
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,480
That's what Hosea says very clearly

759
00:27:40,480 --> 00:27:41,360
He says the land

760
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:43,600
There's no knowledge of God in the land

761
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:45,640
The land is full of idolatry

762
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:49,280
And stealing and robbery and murder and adultery

763
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:50,600
And then he says

764
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:51,800
Who is my quarrel with?

765
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:53,200
Who am I accusing?

766
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:54,640
He says it is you, O priest

767
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:57,680
Because the priests were failing to teach the people

768
00:27:57,680 --> 00:27:59,280
So that's the first task

769
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:00,720
Through the priests

770
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:03,560
God would become known to the people

771
00:28:03,560 --> 00:28:05,480
And then the other direction of course

772
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:07,280
That we're perhaps more familiar with

773
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:08,680
Is that it was the job of the priests

774
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:11,640
To bring the sacrifices of the people to God

775
00:28:11,640 --> 00:28:14,800
Which you read in the first seven chapters of Leviticus

776
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:16,640
So you know this of course

777
00:28:16,640 --> 00:28:18,240
That if you're an Israelite

778
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:20,080
And for some reason

779
00:28:20,080 --> 00:28:22,840
Whether some sin or some uncleanness

780
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:25,400
That you were unable to come into the

781
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:27,320
Worshipping community of God

782
00:28:27,320 --> 00:28:29,720
The temple and so on

783
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:30,640
What would you do?

784
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:32,400
Well you would bring an animal

785
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:35,000
To the sanctuary as prescribed in the law

786
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:38,040
You would lay your hand on its head

787
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:40,400
The priest would be then slaughtered

788
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:42,120
And the blood of the sacrifice

789
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:43,520
Would be thrown against the altar

790
00:28:43,520 --> 00:28:44,960
Representing God

791
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:47,800
And the priest would declare to you

792
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:50,280
That your sin is atoned for

793
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:52,600
Covered or possibly cleansed

794
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:55,720
The word atoned has two possible meanings

795
00:28:55,720 --> 00:28:57,520
And so with the sin dealt with

796
00:28:57,520 --> 00:28:58,720
Through the sacrifice

797
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:00,320
You could then come back

798
00:29:00,320 --> 00:29:02,720
Into covenant fellowship with God

799
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:04,600
And if you offered a fellowship offering

800
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:05,520
As it was called

801
00:29:05,520 --> 00:29:07,480
Then you're going to have a barbecue as well

802
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:10,680
And enjoy a good family meal with the meat

803
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:12,960
That was what it signified

804
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:15,000
Was that you and I are back in fellowship

805
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,640
With God and his people

806
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:18,840
So you can see then that the job of the priest

807
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:19,720
Was twofold

808
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:21,720
It was bringing God to the people

809
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:23,840
And bringing the people to God

810
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:26,520
That was their role within Israel

811
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:30,520
So it's very significant isn't it

812
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:32,240
That God says to the Israelites

813
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:33,720
As a whole people

814
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:35,160
As a community for him

815
00:29:35,160 --> 00:29:37,840
He said you will be for me

816
00:29:37,840 --> 00:29:39,840
To the rest of the nations

817
00:29:39,840 --> 00:29:42,240
What your priests are for you

818
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:45,160
Through you my people Israel

819
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:47,640
I will make myself known to the world

820
00:29:47,640 --> 00:29:49,840
And through you ultimately

821
00:29:49,840 --> 00:29:52,840
I will draw the world to myself

822
00:29:52,840 --> 00:29:56,240
That's what it meant for Israel to be God's priesthood

823
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:57,400
In the midst of the nations

824
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:58,640
At least that's part of the meaning

825
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:01,200
There are other ways of thinking of it as well

826
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:04,920
So as the people of Yahweh God in the Old Testament

827
00:30:04,920 --> 00:30:06,640
They would have this task of

828
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:09,360
Bringing the knowledge of God to the nations

829
00:30:09,360 --> 00:30:10,360
Which they've done

830
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:12,320
Because we've got this book

831
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:14,440
Three quarters of which are the scriptures of Israel

832
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:16,600
Through whom we know the living God

833
00:30:16,600 --> 00:30:19,560
So God has made himself known as it were

834
00:30:19,560 --> 00:30:20,960
Through the priesthood of Israel

835
00:30:20,960 --> 00:30:24,000
Simply being the people that brought us the scriptures

836
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,360
And of course we know

837
00:30:25,360 --> 00:30:26,880
That ultimately it was through Israel

838
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:28,120
The Messiah of Israel

839
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:30,200
The Lord Jesus Christ himself

840
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:32,600
That God has drawn the nations to himself

841
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:33,960
As Jesus put it

842
00:30:33,960 --> 00:30:35,360
That I if I be lifted up

843
00:30:35,360 --> 00:30:37,680
Will draw all men to myself

844
00:30:37,680 --> 00:30:39,680
In his revelation of God

845
00:30:39,680 --> 00:30:42,760
And in his atoning work at the cross

846
00:30:42,760 --> 00:30:45,080
God through the Messiah Jesus

847
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:46,400
Has made himself known

848
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:49,000
And has brought the world to himself

849
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:52,760
So that's the priestly task of this people

850
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:54,360
And even in exile

851
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:57,200
Even when they were thrown out of their land

852
00:30:57,200 --> 00:30:58,560
Under God's judgment

853
00:30:58,560 --> 00:31:00,000
Jeremiah writes them a letter

854
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:02,280
Do you remember in Jeremiah chapter 29

855
00:31:02,280 --> 00:31:04,880
And says that even in the midst of that calamity

