00:52:05,400 --> 00:52:07,400
Who is blind but my servant

1410
00:52:07,400 --> 00:52:09,800
And deaf like the messenger I send

1411
00:52:09,800 --> 00:52:13,200
Who is blind like the one supposedly in covenant with me

1412
00:52:13,200 --> 00:52:15,200
Blind like the servant of the Lord

1413
00:52:15,200 --> 00:52:17,800
And he goes on this is chapter 42

1414
00:52:17,800 --> 00:52:20,800
Who handed over Jacob to become loot

1415
00:52:20,800 --> 00:52:22,600
And Israel to the plunderers

1416
00:52:22,600 --> 00:52:25,800
Was it not the Lord against whom we have sinned

1417
00:52:25,800 --> 00:52:27,800
For they would not follow his ways

1418
00:52:27,800 --> 00:52:29,600
They didn't obey his law

1419
00:52:29,600 --> 00:52:32,400
So he poured out on them his burning anger

1420
00:52:32,400 --> 00:52:34,800
And the violence of war and so on

1421
00:52:34,800 --> 00:52:36,400
And so here is Israel

1422
00:52:36,400 --> 00:52:38,200
Called to be the servant of God

1423
00:52:38,200 --> 00:52:40,600
But languishing in exile

1424
00:52:40,600 --> 00:52:42,400
But says God

1425
00:52:42,400 --> 00:52:46,600
He introduces the servant of the Lord in chapter 42

1426
00:52:46,600 --> 00:52:48,400
And as again you possibly know

1427
00:52:48,400 --> 00:52:50,000
If you studied these chapters

1428
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:53,200
That theme of this servant of the Lord

1429
00:52:53,200 --> 00:52:54,600
Flows through these chapters

1430
00:52:54,600 --> 00:52:56,600
In a mysterious way

1431
00:52:56,600 --> 00:52:59,400
As both being in a sense Israel

1432
00:52:59,400 --> 00:53:01,600
But also being an individual

1433
00:53:01,600 --> 00:53:04,000
Who has a mission to Israel

1434
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:06,800
And indeed through Israel for the nations

1435
00:53:06,800 --> 00:53:08,600
Because in chapter 42

1436
00:53:08,600 --> 00:53:11,400
He's going to bring justice to the nations

1437
00:53:11,400 --> 00:53:15,200
But then that becomes not enough

1438
00:53:15,200 --> 00:53:17,200
Because this is chapter 49

1439
00:53:17,200 --> 00:53:19,600
The Lord says he who formed me in the womb

1440
00:53:19,600 --> 00:53:21,200
To be his servant

1441
00:53:21,200 --> 00:53:23,600
To bring Jacob back to him

1442
00:53:23,600 --> 00:53:25,800
To gather Israel to himself

1443
00:53:25,800 --> 00:53:28,000
So the servant of the Lord

1444
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:30,400
Has a mission to Israel

1445
00:53:30,400 --> 00:53:32,600
To bring Israel back to God

1446
00:53:32,600 --> 00:53:34,800
But in chapter 49

1447
00:53:34,800 --> 00:53:36,400
The servant seems to be struggling

1448
00:53:36,400 --> 00:53:38,400
Because he says I have laboured in vain

1449
00:53:38,400 --> 00:53:40,800
I spent my strength for nothing at all

1450
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:42,800
He has this sense of frustration

1451
00:53:42,800 --> 00:53:45,000
And it gets worse in chapter 50

1452
00:53:45,000 --> 00:53:47,400
Where the servant experiences rejection

1453
00:53:47,400 --> 00:53:49,000
And abuse and people are

1454
00:53:49,000 --> 00:53:50,800
Plucking out his beard and stuff

1455
00:53:50,800 --> 00:53:52,200
So it almost seems

1456
00:53:52,200 --> 00:53:54,000
As if the servant's mission

1457
00:53:54,000 --> 00:53:57,200
Is failing in frustration and opposition

1458
00:53:57,200 --> 00:53:58,800
And then God answers him

1459
00:53:58,800 --> 00:54:00,000
In chapter 49

1460
00:54:00,000 --> 00:54:01,600
With a very startling word

1461
00:54:01,600 --> 00:54:03,000
The Lord says to me

1462
00:54:03,000 --> 00:54:05,400
In answer to that

1463
00:54:05,400 --> 00:54:08,200
It's too small a thing for you to be my servant

1464
00:54:08,200 --> 00:54:10,200
Just to restore the tribes of Jacob

1465
00:54:10,200 --> 00:54:12,600
And to bring back those of Israel that I've kept

1466
00:54:12,600 --> 00:54:16,000
I will also make you a light to the Gentiles

1467
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:18,000
To the nations that my salvation

1468
00:54:18,000 --> 00:54:20,600
May reach the ends of the earth

1469
00:54:20,600 --> 00:54:21,800
I don't know if you've ever had God

1470
00:54:21,800 --> 00:54:22,600
Do that to you

1471
00:54:22,600 --> 00:54:23,600
You know you complain to God

1472
00:54:23,600 --> 00:54:24,600
This is far too hard

1473
00:54:24,600 --> 00:54:25,600
I can't do this

1474
00:54:25,600 --> 00:54:26,600
Because oh really

1475
00:54:26,600 --> 00:54:29,200
Well let me give you something harder

1476
00:54:29,200 --> 00:54:30,400
God sometimes does that

1477
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:32,200
That's what he does to the servant

1478
00:54:32,200 --> 00:54:34,200
He's going to bring Israel back to God

1479
00:54:34,200 --> 00:54:39,400
But also bring the salvation of God to the nations

1480
00:54:39,400 --> 00:54:40,600
So to sum this up

1481
00:54:40,600 --> 00:54:42,000
This servant language then

1482
00:54:42,000 --> 00:54:43,800
Israel as a people

1483
00:54:43,800 --> 00:54:45,000
Was a servant of God

1484
00:54:45,000 --> 00:54:46,800
Chosen upheld by him

1485
00:54:46,800 --> 00:54:48,400
In order to be a light to the nations

1486
00:54:48,400 --> 00:54:50,600
But historically in exile

1487
00:54:50,600 --> 00:54:54,400
Israel was failing in that role in that mission

1488
00:54:54,400 --> 00:54:56,800
Israel as the servant was blind and deaf

1489
00:54:56,800 --> 00:54:58,000
And under God's judgment

1490
00:54:58,000 --> 00:55:00,600
So this individual servant figure

1491
00:55:00,600 --> 00:55:02,600
Mysteriously in the prophet

1492
00:55:02,600 --> 00:55:06,800
Is at one level distinct from Israel

1493
00:55:06,800 --> 00:55:09,000
Because he has a mission to them

1494
00:55:09,000 --> 00:55:10,200
And yet at another level

1495
00:55:10,200 --> 00:55:13,400
Is somehow identified with Israel

1496
00:55:13,400 --> 00:55:15,800
Same language is used of both

1497
00:55:15,800 --> 00:55:17,800
So that the servant figure

1498
00:55:17,800 --> 00:55:22,600
Will actually fulfill the original mission of Israel itself

1499
00:55:22,600 --> 00:55:24,600
That is to bring the salvation

1500
00:55:24,600 --> 00:55:25,600
The justice

1501
00:55:25,600 --> 00:55:27,000
The liberation of God

1502
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:29,400
To the ends of the earth and to all the nations

1503
00:55:29,400 --> 00:55:33,000
The universal purpose of the election of Israel

1504
00:55:33,000 --> 00:55:37,200
Will be accomplished through the servant of Israel

1505
00:55:37,200 --> 00:55:41,200
Now when we come to the New Testament

1506
00:55:41,200 --> 00:55:42,600
There's abundant evidence

1507
00:55:42,600 --> 00:55:44,200
Which I won't try to go into

1508
00:55:44,200 --> 00:55:47,200
To suggest that Jesus saw himself

1509
00:55:47,200 --> 00:55:49,800
In that identity as the servant of the Lord

1510
00:55:49,800 --> 00:55:51,600
In the texts of Isaiah

1511
00:55:51,600 --> 00:55:52,800
For example when he says

1512
00:55:52,800 --> 00:55:55,400
I came not to be served but to serve

1513
00:55:55,400 --> 00:55:58,200
Or I am among you as the one who serves

1514
00:55:58,200 --> 00:55:59,800
And he quotes Isaiah 53

1515
00:55:59,800 --> 00:56:01,200
At the Last Supper and so on

1516
00:56:01,200 --> 00:56:02,800
I haven't time to go there

1517
00:56:02,800 --> 00:56:05,400
But that mission of the servant

1518
00:56:05,400 --> 00:56:08,600
In the Messiah Jesus which he quotes

1519
00:56:08,600 --> 00:56:11,800
Doesn't end with Jesus himself

1520
00:56:11,800 --> 00:56:13,400
Because what we then discover is that

1521
00:56:13,400 --> 00:56:16,200
The Apostle Paul reflected very deeply on these texts

1522
00:56:16,200 --> 00:56:19,800
Also in his mission to the nations

1523
00:56:19,800 --> 00:56:22,000
He saw theologically a link between

1524
00:56:22,000 --> 00:56:25,800
Jesus being the servant who was sent to Israel

1525
00:56:25,800 --> 00:56:27,200
On the one hand

1526
00:56:27,200 --> 00:56:29,400
And the ingathering of the nations

1527
00:56:29,400 --> 00:56:31,600
With great rejoicing to the people of God

1528
00:56:31,600 --> 00:56:34,400
On the other hand he saw them linked together

1529
00:56:34,400 --> 00:56:37,800
That indeed is how he brings his letter to the Romans

1530
00:56:37,800 --> 00:56:39,000
To a climax

1531
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:41,000
A climax which we sometimes ignore

1532
00:56:41,000 --> 00:56:44,400
But it's actually very important in chapter 15

1533
00:56:44,400 --> 00:56:48,600
Where Paul has been saying to the Jewish and Gentile believers

1534
00:56:48,600 --> 00:56:51,200
In chapters 14 through to 15 7

1535
00:56:51,200 --> 00:56:52,200
He's been telling them

1536
00:56:52,200 --> 00:56:53,800
Jews and Gentiles in Christ

1537
00:56:53,800 --> 00:56:56,200
That they must accept one another

1538
00:56:56,200 --> 00:56:57,000
So he says

1539
00:56:57,000 --> 00:57:00,000
I'm now quoting from Romans 15 verse 7

1540
00:57:00,000 --> 00:57:01,400
Accept one another then

1541
00:57:01,400 --> 00:57:04,800
Just as Christ Messiah accepted you

1542
00:57:04,800 --> 00:57:07,200
In order to bring praise to God

1543
00:57:07,200 --> 00:57:09,600
For he says I tell you

1544
00:57:09,600 --> 00:57:13,400
Christ the Messiah has become a servant

1545
00:57:13,400 --> 00:57:15,200
The servant of the Jews

1546
00:57:15,200 --> 00:57:17,600
On behalf of God's truth

1547
00:57:17,600 --> 00:57:19,000
So that

1548
00:57:19,000 --> 00:57:20,000
There's the purpose

1549
00:57:20,000 --> 00:57:23,000
So that the promises made to the patriarchs

1550
00:57:23,000 --> 00:57:24,000
I.e. to Abraham

1551
00:57:24,000 --> 00:57:25,400
Might be confirmed

1552
00:57:25,400 --> 00:57:30,200
Moreover that the nations might glorify God for his mercy

1553
00:57:30,200 --> 00:57:31,400
As it is written

1554
00:57:31,400 --> 00:57:34,200
And then he quotes four Old Testament texts

1555
00:57:34,200 --> 00:57:36,600
Therefore I will praise you among the Gentiles

1556
00:57:36,600 --> 00:57:38,000
And sing praises of your name

1557
00:57:38,000 --> 00:57:40,600
Again it says rejoice you Gentiles with his people

1558
00:57:40,600 --> 00:57:42,800
And again praise the Lord all you Gentiles

1559
00:57:42,800 --> 00:57:44,200
That all the peoples extol him

1560
00:57:44,200 --> 00:57:46,600
And again Isaiah the root of Jesse will spring up

1561
00:57:46,600 --> 00:57:48,200
And he will rule over the nations

1562
00:57:48,200 --> 00:57:50,200
And in him the Gentiles will hope

1563
00:57:50,200 --> 00:57:53,600
Four texts from the law the prophets and the writings

1564
00:57:53,600 --> 00:57:56,600
All of them speaking about God's ultimate purpose

1565
00:57:56,600 --> 00:57:59,600
That the nations the Gentiles will come to rejoice

1566
00:57:59,600 --> 00:58:01,000
And praise God

1567
00:58:01,000 --> 00:58:03,400
And Paul says all of that in a sense

1568
00:58:03,400 --> 00:58:05,600
Is the fulfillment of the fact that

1569
00:58:05,600 --> 00:58:08,400
Jesus became the servant of Israel

1570
00:58:08,400 --> 00:58:09,600
He was the servant

1571
00:58:09,600 --> 00:58:11,800
So that the glory of God

1572
00:58:11,800 --> 00:58:13,600
And the praise of God could go to the nations

1573
00:58:13,600 --> 00:58:15,600
That's how he ends Romans

1574
00:58:15,600 --> 00:58:17,800
It's the climax he brings it to

1575
00:58:17,800 --> 00:58:19,800
And of course Paul could do this

1576
00:58:19,800 --> 00:58:22,200
Because this had been part of his calling

1577
00:58:22,200 --> 00:58:23,800
At the very beginning

1578
00:58:23,800 --> 00:58:26,400
In Acts chapter 26 verse 16

1579
00:58:26,400 --> 00:58:30,200
He knew that he had been called to be a servant and a witness

1580
00:58:30,200 --> 00:58:33,200
The very words that Jesus spoke to him echoed that

1581
00:58:33,200 --> 00:58:35,400
Here's what Jesus said to Saul of Tarsus

1582
00:58:35,400 --> 00:58:37,400
As he still was on the road to Damascus

1583
00:58:37,400 --> 00:58:39,400
Get up stand on your feet

1584
00:58:39,400 --> 00:58:42,000
I've appeared to you to appoint you

1585
00:58:42,000 --> 00:58:43,600
Paul Saul of Tarsus

1586
00:58:43,600 --> 00:58:46,400
As a servant and as a witness

1587
00:58:46,400 --> 00:58:49,200
Of what you have seen and will see of me

1588
00:58:49,200 --> 00:58:50,800
I will rescue you from your own people

1589
00:58:50,800 --> 00:58:52,000
And from the Gentiles

1590
00:58:52,000 --> 00:58:53,800
I'm sending you to them

1591
00:58:53,800 --> 00:58:55,400
The nation the Gentiles

1592
00:58:55,400 --> 00:58:58,000
To open their eyes and turn them from darkness to light

1593
00:58:58,000 --> 00:58:59,800
And from the power of Satan to God

1594
00:58:59,800 --> 00:59:02,000
So that they may receive forgiveness of sins

1595
00:59:02,000 --> 00:59:04,200
And a place among those

1596
00:59:04,200 --> 00:59:06,000
Who are sanctified by faith in me

1597
00:59:06,000 --> 00:59:07,800
Paul himself

1598
00:59:07,800 --> 00:59:10,200
Was commissioned to be servant and witness

1599
00:59:10,200 --> 00:59:11,800
And that's why

1600
00:59:11,800 --> 00:59:13,800
When Paul was in a synagogue

1601
00:59:13,800 --> 00:59:15,800
In Pisidia in Antioch

1602
00:59:15,800 --> 00:59:18,400
And he had given the whole history of Israel

1603
00:59:18,400 --> 00:59:19,800
In about seven verses

1604
00:59:19,800 --> 00:59:20,800
To the people there

1605
00:59:20,800 --> 00:59:23,400
And led it from Abraham right up to Jesus

1606
00:59:23,400 --> 00:59:25,800
And said this is what has now been fulfilled

1607
00:59:25,800 --> 00:59:27,800
And some of the Jews believed him

1608
00:59:27,800 --> 00:59:28,800
And some would not

1609
00:59:28,800 --> 00:59:30,400
And the following Sabbath

1610
00:59:30,400 --> 00:59:33,200
They came back and some of them opposed him

1611
00:59:33,200 --> 00:59:36,600
And Paul what he does is that he takes this text

1612
00:59:36,600 --> 00:59:38,200
From Isaiah

1613
00:59:38,200 --> 00:59:41,200
Which of course he knew had been fulfilled by Jesus

1614
00:59:41,200 --> 00:59:43,200
And he applies it to himself

1615
00:59:43,200 --> 00:59:45,800
And his little band of missionary friends

1616
00:59:45,800 --> 00:59:49,600
He moves from Jesus as the true son of David and Messiah

1617
00:59:49,600 --> 00:59:50,800
And his resurrection

1618
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:54,400
Through to the God-fearing Gentiles in the audience

1619
00:59:54,400 --> 00:59:57,000
This is his words, Acts 13

1620
00:59:57,000 --> 00:59:59,800
We now turn to the Gentiles

1621
00:59:59,800 --> 01:00:03,800
For this is what the Lord has commanded us, he says

1622
01:00:03,800 --> 01:00:07,000
I have made you a light for the Gentiles

1623
01:00:07,000 --> 01:00:10,000
That you may bring my salvation to the ends of the earth

1624
01:00:10,000 --> 01:00:13,000
That's what God has commanded us, says Paul

1625
01:00:13,000 --> 01:00:16,000
And we've been doing our exegesis and hermeneutics class

1626
01:00:16,000 --> 01:00:17,800
We might say, just a minute Paul

1627
01:00:17,800 --> 01:00:21,200
Isaiah actually said that about Old Testament Israel

1628
01:00:21,200 --> 01:00:22,800
Paul said, yeah I know that

1629
01:00:22,800 --> 01:00:25,000
And Jesus we understand

1630
01:00:25,000 --> 01:00:27,800
Jesus applied the language of the servant to himself

1631
01:00:27,800 --> 01:00:29,200
And Paul said, yeah I know that too

1632
01:00:29,200 --> 01:00:31,600
I've just said it in chapter 15

1633
01:00:31,600 --> 01:00:33,200
But here Paul says

1634
01:00:33,200 --> 01:00:36,600
That this command of the servant to Israel through Jesus

1635
01:00:36,600 --> 01:00:41,000
Is now also explicitly the command for God's people

1636
01:00:41,000 --> 01:00:44,000
And we are to be that servant people

1637
01:00:44,000 --> 01:00:46,000
Bringing the light of God to the nations

1638
01:00:46,000 --> 01:00:48,600
It is a missional text for the church

1639
01:00:48,600 --> 01:00:52,000
As the servant of the Lord bearing witness to him

1640
01:00:52,000 --> 01:00:53,200
So there we are

1641
01:00:53,200 --> 01:00:56,400
Once again I hope what we've seen is that

1642
01:00:56,400 --> 01:00:58,800
In the scriptures of Israel and the Old Testament

1643
01:00:58,800 --> 01:01:01,400
We find some essential understandings

1644
01:01:01,400 --> 01:01:03,000
Of what it means not just to be

1645
01:01:03,000 --> 01:01:04,400
The people of God

1646
01:01:04,400 --> 01:01:06,600
But for the purpose for which we are

1647
01:01:06,600 --> 01:01:07,800
The people of God

1648
01:01:07,800 --> 01:01:10,600
Rooted in God's missional purpose for Israel

1649
01:01:10,600 --> 01:01:14,000
Like them we are called in partnership with God

1650
01:01:14,000 --> 01:01:16,200
For the nations and to the nations

1651
01:01:16,200 --> 01:01:19,000
To be a blessing, to be a priesthood

1652
01:01:19,000 --> 01:01:22,400
To be a witness and to be God's servant

1653
01:01:22,400 --> 01:01:24,600
May God help us to do that

1654
01:01:24,600 --> 01:01:27,000
For his name's sake, amen

1655
